<br>
Change and growth are intregal aspects of the Cycle of Creation, and now we find them among us.  The Draconian adventurers formerly known as &quot;Team Draconis,&quot; a group I have had honored to be a part of, are in the midst of Change.  We are, and remain, friends and family, but have different goals and interests, and must follow those as we are guided.<br>
<br>
Jyllianne is returning to her new home, Katta Castellum to give birth and pursue interests there (congratulations early Jyll, I DO hope they are twins <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Pipette is travelling with her, but also feels the solitary call of the wild.  After much consideration and reflection, I have decided to retain my rooms in Thurgadin on Velious for the time being.<br>
<br>
I have been discussing with other Draconians (and future Draconians /smiles at Kam) about banding together for common interests and companionship.  For example, Keskan and I have been talking about hunting griffins in the Eastern Wastes for their eggs much needed by the Coldain.  It is my belief that joining with others of our large family only serves to strengthen and educate oneself in the varied means of combat and tactics.  I welcome this change, and the chance to meld old companions with new ones.<br>
<br>
As always, if any of Draconis have need of my skills or services, I stand ready to serve how I might.  I admire and respect you all, and wish you the brightest of journeys, wherever those roads may take you.<br>
<br>
HAIL DRACONIS!<br>
